This paper focuses on linguistic analysis of textual discussions, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The use of binary classifiers and feature selection techniques also suggests a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence (AI). The analysis of function words and pronouns indicates a possible connection to information retrieval (IR) and sentiment analysis. The use of Wikipedia data suggests a possible connection to social media analysis (SI). Finally, the focus on communication styles and language use suggests a possible connection to computational linguistics (LG).
